  "texts": [
    "8,73 have investigated the number of all possible valid combinations that can be created by using the elements acquired so far as a proxy of the level of innovation of a given system.",
    "In this way, the potential for new discoveries is accounted for, rather than the actual number of novel combinations observed in a system and their rate of appearance.",
    "As we have shown through the analysis of empirical sequences of music listening records, higher-order Heaps' exponents can be used to further classify users of Last.fm with the same rate of discovery of new songs or new artists.",
    "The higher-order Heaps' exponent can indeed tell apart different ways to explore the same set of songs in terms of number of different associations of consecutive pairs or triples of songs.",
    "Analogously, we found that higher-order Heaps' exponents can uncover different patterns in the use of words in different texts."
  ],
